    <section id="types_of_proposals_listed_in_the_content_completi">
      <title>Types of Proposals Listed in the Content Completion Assistant</title>
      <p>The <wintitle>Content Completion Assistant</wintitle> offers the following types of
        proposed actions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Insert allowed elements for the current context  schema and the list of proposals
          contains elements depending on the elements inserted both before and after the cursor
          position. </li>
        <li>Insert element values if such values are specified in the schema for the current
          context.</li>
        <li>Insert new undeclared elements by entering their name in the text field.</li>
        <li>Insert CDATA sections, comments, processing instructions.</li>
        <li>Insert <xref href="../topics/code-templates.dita#code-templates" format="dita">code
            templates</xref>.</li>
        <?oxy_insert_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T121849+0300"?>
        <li><ph conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/proposal-type-rename"/></li>
        <li><ph conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/proposal-type-surround"/></li>
        <?oxy_insert_end?>
        <?oxy_delete author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T121953+0300" content="&lt;li&gt;If invoked on a selection containing only an element start or end tag, it will allow you to rename the element.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If invoked on a selection of elements or other content, it will allow you to surround the content with certain tags.&lt;/li&gt;"?>
        <li>If the <xref
            href="preferences-schema-aware.dita#preferences-schema-aware/show-all-possible-elements"
              ><uicontrol>Show all possible elements in the content completion list</uicontrol>
            option from the <uicontrol>Schema-Aware</uicontrol> preferences page</xref> is enabled,
          the content completion pop-up window will present all the elements defined by the schema.
          When choosing an element from this section, the insertion will be performed using the
          schema-aware smart editing features.<note>By default, you are not allowed to insert
            element names that are not defined by the schema. This can be changed by deselecting the
              <xref
              href="preferences-schema-aware.dita#preferences-schema-aware/allow-only-insertion"
                ><uicontrol>Allow only insertion of valid elements and attributes</uicontrol> check
              box from the <uicontrol>Schema-Aware</uicontrol> preferences page</xref>.</note></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="examples_of_how_the_content_completion_assistant_">
      <title><?oxy_comment_start author="george" timestamp="20160330T100133+0300" comment="The rename and surround below should duplicate the above info and in this section I think they are very generic, I expect specific examples here." id="ocl_fhm_mv"?><?oxy_comment_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T112753+0300" comment="I will work with Steven to give some examples (most likely in the form of screenshots taken when editing a DITA topic)." parentID="ocl_fhm_mv" mid="5"?>Examples
        of How the Content Completion Assistant
        Works<?oxy_comment_end mid="5"?><?oxy_comment_end?></title>
      <fig>
        <title>Content Completion Assistant</title>
        <image href="../img/author_content_completion.png"/>
      </fig>
      <p>To illustrate how the feature works, consider the following examples of invoking the
          <wintitle>Content Completion Assistant</wintitle> in certain contexts:<ul>
          <li>The first entry in the <wintitle>Content Completion Assistant</wintitle> is often a
              <uicontrol>Split &lt;Element name&gt;</uicontrol> item. In most cases, you can only
            split the closest block element to the cursor position, but if it is inside a list item,
            the list item will also be proposed for split. Selecting <uicontrol>Split &lt;Element
              name&gt;</uicontrol> splits the content of the specified element around the cursor
            position.
            <?oxy_comment_start author="george" timestamp="20160330T094942+0300" comment="In this case the action changes in New &lt;Element name&gt;." flag="done"?><?oxy_delete author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T105410+0300" flag="done" content="Thus, if the cursor is positioned at the beginning or at the end of the element, the newly created sibling will be empty."?><?oxy_comment_end?><?oxy_insert_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T105411+0300" flag="done"?>
            However, if the cursor is positioned at the beginning or at the end of the element, the
            action, the first item offered in the Content Completion Assistant is <uicontrol>New
              &lt;Element name&gt;</uicontrol>. Selecting this item will insert an empty
            element.<?oxy_insert_end?></li>
          <li>If the cursor is positioned inside a
            <?oxy_comment_start author="george" timestamp="20160330T095049+0300" comment="maybe add &quot;a code block for example&quot;." flag="done"?>space
            preserved
            element<?oxy_insert_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T103009+0300" flag="done"?>
            (for example a code block)<?oxy_insert_end?>,<?oxy_comment_end?> the first choice in the
              <wintitle>Content Completion Assistant</wintitle> is <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>,
            which will insert a new line in the content of the element.</li>
          <li><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="235,192,230"?><?oxy_delete author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T122015+0300" content="If you invoke content completion on a selected element start or end tag, a &lt;uicontrol&gt;Rename&lt;/uicontrol&gt; operation can be performed. The &lt;wintitle&gt;Content Completion Assistant&lt;/wintitle&gt; will propose a list of elements that can be selected to replace the original element. "?></li>
          <?oxy_insert_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T122018+0300" comment="Example/screenshot needed here."?>
          <li><ph conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/proposal-type-rename"/></li>
          <?oxy_insert_end?>
          <li><?oxy_delete author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T122031+0300" content="If you invoke content completion on a selection of elements or other content, a &lt;uicontrol&gt;Surround with&lt;/uicontrol&gt; operation can be performed. The &lt;wintitle&gt;Content Completion Assistant&lt;/wintitle&gt; will propose a list of elements that can be selected to surround the content."?><?oxy_custom_end?></li>
          <?oxy_insert_start author="bogdan" timestamp="20160331T122032+0300" comment="Example/screenshot needed here."?>
          <li><ph conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/proposal-type-surround"/></li>
          <?oxy_insert_end?>
        </ul></p>
